Package mmj.util

Class RunParmArrayEntry

java.lang.Object
mmj.util.RunParmArrayEntry
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<RunParmArrayEntry>
public class RunParmArrayEntry extends Object implements Comparable<RunParmArrayEntry>
RunParmArrayEntry holds a RunParm "name" string AND an array(0->n) of RunParm "value" strings, OR it holds a "commentLine" (but not both).

  • Field Details

    • commentLine

      public String commentLine
      if commentLine != null then the entire entry is a comment and there is no data in the rest of it. This is the case when the first character of the input line is a blank or the line is empty.

    • name

      public String name
      name is the first field on a DelimitedTextParser line.

      Generally, this would be a keyword.

    • cmd

      public BatchCommand cmd

    • values

      public String[] values
      values is an array of String corresponding to fields 1 -> n of a DelimitedTextParser.

      The program knows nothing about the contents of fields except that they are String's, and perhaps empty ("").

  • Constructor Details

    • RunParmArrayEntry

      public RunParmArrayEntry()
      Construct a dummy RunParmArrayEntry with no parameters.

    • RunParmArrayEntry

      public RunParmArrayEntry(String name, String[] values)
      Construct a RunParmArrayEntry manually using a name and values array.

      Quoter and Delimiter characters are set to the defaults from UtilConstants:

      • UtilConstants.RUNPARM_FIELD_DELIMITER_DEFAULT
      • UtilConstants.RUNPARM_FIELD_QUOTER_DEFAULT
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the RunParm
      values - the arguments to the RunParm

    • RunParmArrayEntry

      public RunParmArrayEntry(DelimitedTextParser parser)
      Construct a RunParmArrayEntry using a DelimitedTextParser pre-loaded with text line and delimiter/quoter parms.

      Checks for comment: if the input line begins with one of the following characters then it is deemd a "comment":

      • UtilConstants.RUNPARM_COMMENT_CHAR_SPACE
      • UtilConstants.RUNPARM_COMMENT_CHAR_ASTERISK
      • UtilConstants.RUNPARM_COMMENT_CHAR_SLASH

      If the line is not a comment but is empty or null, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown. Otherwise, the name and values are extracted using DelimitedTextParser.

      Parameters:
      parser - pre-loaded DelimitedTextParser object.
